  <section class="page-intro section-shell">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Imran Ibrahimli</h1>
    <p>
      I’m interested in deep learning, representation learning, and mechanistic
      explanations that survive contact with experiments.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-grid section-shell">
    <div class="about-prose">
      <p>
        This site is a public research notebook: part replication log, part
        technical essay, and part forcing function for clearer thinking. The
        aim is not to publish a polished answer every time. It is to state the
        question precisely, show the evidence, and separate observation from
        interpretation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Expect small controlled experiments, plots that earn their space,
        readable derivations, and links to code. When a result is preliminary
        or illustrative, I’ll say so.
      </p>
    </div>
